reviewText: Booty Call is one of the funniest urban films ever made. Jamie Foxx had his first starring role in this film and he showed that he could carry a movie. Tommy Davidson plats second string to Foxx but the two make a great comic team and Vivca Fox is also very sexy in this movie. One has to wonder what would happened if Chris Tucker would have taken this movie on instead of Rush Hour.
summary: One of the funniest films of the late nineties

reviewText: Booty Call is one of the initial movie appearances of Jamie Foxx and Tommy Davidson after starring on Living Color.  Don't expect high-brow comedy as this is a comedy that stretches the boundary of good taste and common sense, but it is funny nonetheless.  Some of the scenes are destine to be classics, such as the 7-11 scenes, the plastic wrap, and the impressions scenes.  If you are easily offended and easily embarrassed then this is not the movie for you.  But if you take it for what it is, a silly comedy, then you will find yourself laughing out loud.

reviewText: A pair of stupid men are anxious to get laid.  A pair of girls are willing enough, and surprisingly supportive considering how amazingly stupid the guys are.  They wrap themselves in plastic wrap as a form of birth control.  This made you laugh?  It's so dumb.  Does dumb mean funny?  I guess so, to  some people.  The point seems to be that no matter how stupid a guy is, he  is entitled to get serviced by girls he isn't marrying.  Yeah, okay, but  where are the laughs?
